Task: Build the Support Ticket system for the Corefinity Control Panel, including both the Ticket Listing and Ticket Detail View.
вЂ‹1. Ticket Listing Page:
вЂ‹Create a table showing: Subject, Created Date, Last Update, Priority, and Status.
вЂ‹Include filter buttons at the top for Status (e.g., All, Open, Pending, Closed).
вЂ‹Make the Subject an OrangeLink that navigates to the detailed view.
вЂ‹Ensure table headers are clickable for sorting.
вЂ‹2. Ticket Detail View (Layout):
вЂ‹Top Bar: Display Ticket Title and Status.
вЂ‹Context Sidebar: On the right side, show a "Ticket Info" box with associated links:
вЂ‹Agency: [OrangeLink]
вЂ‹Company: [OrangeLink]
вЂ‹Website: [OrangeLink]
вЂ‹Tabbed Detail: Create two tabs: Conversation and History. (History should contain a log of status changes to keep the main chat clean).
вЂ‹3. Strict Requirement: The "Dual-Input" Messaging Box:
вЂ‹Create a messaging interface at the bottom of the Conversation tab.
вЂ‹Constraint: Clearly distinguish between an "Internal Note" and a "Customer Reply."
вЂ‹UI Implementation: >    - Provide a toggle or two distinct tabs above the text area: "Internal Comment" (Staff Only) and "Send Reply" (Visible to Client).
вЂ‹When "Internal Comment" is active, change the background of the text area to a subtle Light Yellow and change the button to "Post Internal Note."
вЂ‹When "Send Reply" is active, use the standard Corefinity Blue/Orange button.
вЂ‹4. Chat Styling:
вЂ‹Style the conversation like a modern thread (similar to Jira or Zendesk).
вЂ‹Use different background colors for messages from the "User" vs. "Corefinity Support."
